    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 2nd with a focus on exploiting speed and favorable matchups, headlined by our strongest play, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.96). He remains a must-start, benefiting significantly from a soft matchup against R. Nelson and a dynamic platoon advantage that pushes his efficiency well into the \"Strong\" tier. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (67.10) and **Colt Keith** (66.91) anchor the middle of our order, with **Junior Caminero** surging due to an elite #2 lineup spot and **Colt Keith** capitalizing on Kumar Rocker\u2019s slow delivery, which creates prime conditions for stolen bases\u2014a critical priority for our roster strategy. Meanwhile, **Caleb Durbin** (63.88) earns a start despite a lower lineup placement because his matchup against Arrighetti offers a massive +19% boost in SP skill efficiency, making him our primary utility weapon for today\u2019s card.\n\nThe bench decision process was narrow, with **Chase Meidroth** (47.06) serving as the final cut. While **Chase Meidroth** projected respectably, the optimizer ultimately favored the higher-upside platoon splits offered by **Josh Smith** (60.52) and **Luke Raley** (51.70). We are monitoring several \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Junior Caminero**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Josh Smith**, and **Luke Raley**; should any of these players drop lower in their respective lineups, their efficiency scores will adjust downward accordingly. Furthermore, while **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88) remains a fixture, his matchup against Early is suppressed by a tough L/L platoon disadvantage and an elite SP xERA of 2.97. **Christian Yelich** remains shelved on the IL, but we continue to monitor the rotation of **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** as we look for further opportunities to bolster our stolen base output.",
